New Records: David Warner became Australia's all-time leading run-scorer in T20Is by scoring 56 against Oman.
The match is played on a new surface at Kensington Oval, which is the best available.
Key Match Events: High-pressure clash between defending champions England and Australia, who are also world title-holders in Test and ODI cricket.
Pre-Game Insights: England is under pressure after a rain-affected match against Scotland.
Australia's probable XI includes Pat Cummins returning and Nathan Ellis potentially sitting out.
Teams may need to adapt to difficult batting conditions due to the surface.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is significant in the context of the tournament and has historical importance.
The atmosphere is expected to be intense with many English fans in attendance.
Others: England have a slight edge in their T20I head-to-head record with Australia.
There have been only two 200-plus scores in T20Is at Kensington Oval in the same match between England and West Indies in 2022.
